http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Students-told-to-develop-a-sense-of-curiosity/article13989617.ece

The students of Swami Vivekananda School were asked to develop a sense of curiosity and scientific temper to shape their future career.Professor at Kakatiya University, Ram Reddy, was addressing the students at Hanamkonda during their annual science fair held on Friday.He wanted them to explore, discover and invent things that would help humanity.Shyam Sunder Reddy of Regional Science Centre wanted the students to develop the habit of reading and gain knowledge which will help them in a long-term.School principal Uma Rao talked about the life of Swami Vivekananda and emphasised that students should develop their personality in a way that would help them achieve what they want.Directors K. Somi Reddy, K. Sadashiva Reddy, Thota Venkateshwarlu Garu, Manikya Rao Garu and teachers were present.